      <title>2048 - Open Source Puzzle Game</title>
      <link href="/2026/04/24/Source%20Puzzle%20Game/"/>
      <url>/2026/04/24/Source%20Puzzle%20Game/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="About-the-Game"><a href="#About-the-Game" class="headerlink" title="About the Game"></a>About the Game</h2><p>2048 is a simple, addictive, and open-source number puzzle game. Slide tiles to combine the same numbers and try to reach the 2048 tile.</p><p>It runs entirely in the browser — no installation, no ads, no account required.</p><h2 id="How-to-Play"><a href="#How-to-Play" class="headerlink" title="How to Play"></a>How to Play</h2><ul><li>Desktop: Arrow keys (↑ ↓ ← →)</li><li>Mobile: Swipe screen</li><li>Refresh page to restart</li></ul><h2 id="Play-Online"><a href="#Play-Online" class="headerlink" title="Play Online"></a>Play Online</h2><p><a href="https://play2048.co/">Play Now</a></p><h2 id="Open-Source-Info"><a href="#Open-Source-Info" class="headerlink" title="Open Source Info"></a>Open Source Info</h2><ul><li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/gabrielecirulli/2048">https://github.com/gabrielecirulli/2048</a></li><li>License: MIT (free &amp; open-source)</li></ul>]]></content>
      
      
